Responsible for the supervision and management of the product, technology and security function. Represent the technology strategy and agenda of our clients Business.
Demonstrating ethical leadership and business integrity;
Managing and implementing business and technical operations;
Creating management reports based on key performance metrics;
Sharing strategic leadership responsibilities with the Executive Leadership Team and other strategic managers and ensuring technology enables business at a strategic and operational level;
Engaging and communicating effectively with colleagues, investors, customers, suppliers, regulators and other internal and external stakeholders;
Be an active member of various committees including Audit Committee and Outsourcing Committee
Work with the security function in the creation of new information security policies and procedures when needs arise;
Work with the security function to maintain and update existing information security policies and procedures;
Reviewing policies owned by the function on an annual basis and assist with the policy approval process;
Conducting an annual risk assessment that identifies major strategic developments in the industry, emerging threats, and vulnerabilities to business and IT assets of the Entity, as well as all third-party vendors and partners, and report results in a formal risk assessment document;
Creation, maintenance and distribution of the incident response and escalation procedures for information security and IT incidents;
Ensuring that security alerts are monitored and analysed and that this information is distributed to appropriate information security, technical and business unit management personnel;
Ensuring that daily incident logs are reviewed on an ongoing basis and identified exceptions are followed up;
Controlling and monitoring access to restricted areas and confidential data;
Ensure appropriate physical controls are in place where customer information is present;
Oversee annual testing, including internal and external scans and penetration testing, testing related to emerging risks such as cyber and new technologies, such as, API;
Managing the process for evolving the incident response plan according to lessons learned and in response to industry development;
Work with the security function to maintain a formal security awareness program, which includes periodic training for all staff members, that provides multiple methods of communicating awareness and educating employees (for example, posters, letters, meetings);
Ensure technology selection (in-sourced or out-sourced) are in line with the business and operational objectives of the company and will monitor the relationship with outsourcing parties on an ongoing basis.
Ensuring that all third parties with whom data is shared, are managed and monitored accordingly; and
Continuously monitoring concentration risk of key IT providers and revise contingency and exit plans to cater for performance issues or the failure of an outsourced party.
